 323: Then they were moving again. Out the door. Up the cor ridor. Left then right. Left then right. Through the brightly lit government maze, stepping over the bodies they had killed on their way in. In the space of ninety seconds, they arrived back at the underground garage, where they all piled back into the van, together with their prize. No sooner was the last man's feet inside than the van's wheels skidded against the concrete and the big vehicle peeled away from 
 324: 
 325: the loading dock and sped out into the night. 
