2900: 
2901: 'Like many other South American cultures, the Incans had an unusual fascination with the great cats. They built statues to them, both large and small, and sometimes they carved huge has reliefs of them into entire mountain rock- faces. Why, the city of Cuzco was even built in the shape of a puma. 
2902: 
