3800: 
3801: 
3802: 
3803: Race crossed the rope bridge last of all, holding onto the safety rope so hard his knuckles went white. As such, he crossed the bridge more slowly than the others, so by the time he stepped onto the ledge on the other side, they had already gone on ahead and all he saw was a damp stone stairway leading up into the foliage. He hurried up it after them. 
3804: 
3805: Dripping green leaves crowded in on either side of him. 
3806: 
3807: Wet fern fronds slapped against his face as he climbed the watersoaked stone slabs after the others. After about thirty seconds of climbing, he burst through a large set of branches and found himself standing in a small clearing of some sort. 
3808: 
3809: Everyone else was already there. But they just stood there, motionless. At first Race didn't know what had made them stop, but then he saw that they all had their flashlights pointed up and to the left. 
3810: 
3811: His gaze followed their flashlight beams and he saw it. 
3812: 
3813: 'Holy Christ,' he breathed. 
3814: 
3815: There, situated on the highest point of the rock tower— covered in hard-packed mud and moss, concealed by weeds all around it, and glistening wet in the ever-falling rain— stood an ominous stone structure. 
3816: 
3817: It was cloaked in shadow and wetness, but it was clear that this was a structure that had been designed to exude menace and power. A structure that could have had no other purpose than to inspire fear, idolatry and worship. 
3818: 
3819: It was a temple. 
3820: 
3821: 
3822: 
3823: Race stared at the dark stone temple and swallowed hard. 
