3828: 
3829: It wasn't a very big structure. In fact, it was barely even one storey tall. But Race knew that wasn't really the case. 
3830: 
3831: He guessed what they were seeing was only the very top of the temple—the tip of the iceberg—because the ruined section of it that they now saw finished too abruptly. It just disappeared into the mud beneath their feet. 
3832: 
3833: Race presumed that the rest of the enormous structure lay buried in the mud beneath them, consumed by four hundred years of accumulated wet earth. 
3834: 
