15626: 
15627: The men—they were Navy SEALs—hit the ground first, followed a split second later by the massive helicopter as it came crashing down on top of them, crushing them in an instant, its awesome bulk slamming down against the ground with a resounding whump! 
15628: 
15629: Race looked above the fallen, flaming wreck of the Super Stallion and saw a horizontal smoke-trail dissipating in the air above it. 
15630: 
15631: It was the smoke-trail of an air-to-air missile. Race traced it back to its source. 
15632: 
15633: And saw another helicopter! 
15634: 
15635: 
15636: 
15637: Only this one wasn't a troop transport like the two Super Stallions. It was a two-man chopper—an attack bird—thin but not skinny, with a prism-shaped cockpit and an enclosed tail rotor. It looked like a mechanical preying mantis. 
15638: 
15639: Although Race didn't know it, he was looking at an AH-66 'Comanche'—the U.S. Army's next-generation attack helicopter. 
15640: 
15641: Nash's air support. 
15642: 
