15748: 
15749: 
15750: 
15751: grasp, bared its jaws and launched itself at his head. Out of sheer desperation, Doogie swung his G-11 around and without even thinking, wedged it inside the big crocodilian's mouth, 
15752: 
15753: propping it open, right in front of his own face! 
15754: 
15755: The caiman grunted in surprise. 
15756: 
15757: Its jaws were now propped wide open, like the bonnet of a car. The big creature couldn't close its mouth! 
15758: 
15759: Doogie seized the opportunity and quickly unsheathed his Bowie knife. 
15760: 
15761: The caiman stood stupidly in front of him, its long snout held open by the vertical G11. 
15762: 
15763: Doogie tried to get around the big reptile—behind it—so that he could drive his knife into its skull and kill it, but the caiman saw him move and it swung quickly sideways, bowling into him, knocking him off his feet, sending him splashing into the muddy water. 
15764: 
15765: The caiman then stomped quickly forward, stepping on top of Doogie's legs with its stubby forelimbs, causing them to sink down into the mud. 
15766: 
