17604: 
17605: In the cargo bay, the world tilted crazily. Race saw the damage that he'd done, saw where this plane was going. 
17606: 
17607: While I've still got one second left, I'm going to try to disarm that bomb. 
17608: 
17609: Bittiker was still standing on the skirt of the tank, still holding his Calico pistol, but he'd been thrown wildly off balance by the discharge of the cannon. 
17610: 
