18120: 
18121: a gigantic stone-walled cavern that had been carved out of 
18122: 
18123: the belly of the rock tower. 
18124: 
18125: It was absolutely spectacular. 
18126: 
18127: An enormous, rock-walled cathedral. 
18128: 
18129: Its high vaulted ceiling soared into the air at least fifty feet 
18130: 
18131: above the floor, disappearing into darkness. It was supported 
18132: 
18133: by a set of stone columns that had been fashioned out of the 
18134: 
18135: 
18136: 
18137: rock. A flat stone floor stretched away from Race. It also disappeared into shadow. 
18138: 
18139: The walls of the cathedral, however, were its most stunning feature. 
18140: 
18141: They were covered with primitive carvings—pictographs similar to those that adorned the portal up on the surface. 
18142: 
18143: There were pictures of rapas, pictures of people, pictures of rapas killing people. Tearing their limbs off, ripping their heads off. In some of the carvings, the screaming humans being mauled by the cats clutched piles of loot in their hands, even as they were being killed. 
18144: 
18145: Wanton greed, even at the moment of death. 
18146: 
18147: Interspersed among the carvings on the walls were a series of stone alcoves that had all been carved in the shape of rapas' heads. 
18148: 
18149: Thick cobwebs covered each alcove, so that it looked as if see-through grey curtains had been lowered over the carved rapas' jaws. 
18150: 
18151: Race went over to one of the alcoves, sliced through the 
18152: 
18153: cobweb across the rapa's mouth. 
18154: 
18155: His eyes widened. 
18156: 
18157: A small shelf-like podium had been carved into the wall inside the rapa's bared jaws, On it sat a lustrous golden statue that had been fashioned in the shape of a fat man with an enormous erection. 
18158: 
18159: 'Good God…' he breathed as he stared at the statue. 
18160: 
18161: He scanned the hall around him. There must have been forty such alcoves scattered around its walls. And if there was an artefact in each one, then it would be a treasure that was worth… 
18162: 
18163: It was Solon's treasure. 
18164: 
18165: Race looked at the ornate alcove in front of him, looked at the carved rapa's head, snarling viciously at him. 
18166: 
