18208: 
18209: olive-skinned corpses on the pile. 
18210: 
18211: Natives. 
18212: 
18213: And then suddenly he saw a small hole in the wall beyond the grisly pile of bodies. 
18214: 
18215: It was roughly circular in shape, about two-andhalf-feet in diameter, the width of a broadshouldered man. 
18216: 
18217: Race immediately recalled seeing a similarly shaped stone up on the surface earlier—on the balcony-like path behind the temple—a peculiar round stone amid all the square-shaped ones, a stone that appeared to have been 
18218: 
18219: slotted into a cylindrical hole of some sort. Oh, no, Race thought, realising. 
18220: 
18221: It wasn't a hole… 
18222: 
18223: 
18224: 
