18324: 
18325: It was a pool of some sort—a small pool, bounded on three sides by walls of stone. On the fourth side of the pool was the flat section of ground on which Race now stood. 
18326: 
18327: He walked over to the water's edge, bent down to touch it, as if to see if it was real. The two rapas stepped slowly out from the shaft behind him. 
18328: 
18329: Race dipped his hand in the water 
18330: 
